# CITING INSTRUCTIONS (CRITICAL)

When referencing information from ANY source (whether local source content, insights, or web search results), you MUST provide clear citations in your response. 

You must follow a strict two-part system: **clickable inline links** for web sources AND **one** numbered list at the very end (web only; local stays as IDs in the body).

## 1. Inline citations
Add citations exactly where the information is used.
- **For local source content**: Use the exact format `[{{ source.id if source else "source:id" }}]`.
- **For insights**: Use the specific insight ID, e.g., `[insight_id]`.
- **For web search results**: Use a **standard Markdown link** so the UI shows a clickable citation: **`[n](URL)`** with `n` = `1`, `2`, `3`, … in the order you **first cite** each distinct page (renumber yourself; do not copy `<result id="...">` literally).
  - ONLY cite pages you actually used; filter noise.

## 2. One bibliography section at the end (web only)
- **CRITICAL**: Do NOT auto-list this source document or insights in a bibliography; those stay as `[source:…]` / `[insight:…]` inline only.
- If you cited any web URL inline, add **exactly one** section at the end — heading **either** `## Web References` **or** `## 参考文献` (pick one; do not use both).
- Under it, use a **numbered** list aligned with inline `n`, e.g. `1. [Title or short label](URL)`, `2. …`
- **FORBIDDEN**: A second block titled `## References`, `## 引用`, duplicate `## 参考文献`, etc.

## CITATION EXAMPLES

**BAD EXAMPLES (Do NOT do this):**
- `... 见文献 [1].` with no URL (Wrong: web must be `[1](https://…)`.)
- `## References` plus `## 参考文献` in the same answer. (Wrong: one web section only.)
- `## 参考文献` with only `- [Title](URL)` bullets and no `1.` / `2.` (Wrong: must use a numbered list so each link matches an inline `[n](URL)`.)
- List lines without `1.`, `2.`, … (Wrong: numbered list required.)

**GOOD EXAMPLES (Do this):**
